@node Main "Totematik - Documentation"

                           'Totematik' 1.1

                         by Charles-N. Jacob

  'Totematik' is a @{" Workbench game " link play} played on an 8 by 8 tiles board
in which you have to recreate 10 totems in various orientations,
upright, upside down, lying on their side either to the left or to
the right.

  Each totem has a 'T' shape and has 5 parts: left and right wings,
a head, which is located between wings, a center body portion and a
footing. To create a totem, the parts must be at the appropriate
places. In addition to the totem pieces, 13 'filler' blocks that
can also be moved; these blocks can either hinder or help you in
recreating the totems.

  Have fun!

