@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Totematik" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your
Workbench must have at least 8 colours.

NOTE: I am not sure about the game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Totematik runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with
      a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, just click on any tile located next to the empty space,
if the move is possible, the clicked tile will go there. Please
note that you can use the cursor keys to move the tiles...

  Each totem has a 'T' shape and includes 5 parts: a left wing, a
right wing (both have a triangular shape), a head which is located
between the wings (it has a cross shape), a center body portion
located under the head and a footing, which is the lowest part.

  To create a totem, the parts must be at their appropriate places:
the wings must be placed so their straight portions are located on
either side and in line with the upper portion of the head part of
a totem. The center body portion has an 'angle' displayed on the
middle and that angle must be pointed toward the head of the totem.
As for the foot part, obviously it will have to be located at the
base of the totem. To make matters simpler, depending on the
orientation of a totem, all associated parts have the same colour,
so you can see which parts goes with which totem.

  In addition to the totem parts, 13 'filler' blocks can be moved
as you wish, these blocks and their position have no importance
whatsoever, they are just there to help or complicate the game...

  A display, on the lower right in the window, shows the number of
totems that are currently recreated, when that number gets to 10,
the game is complete! ...Try to recreate all totems in the minimum
amount of moves.

  Note that you can restart a game anytime by clicking on the
'New Game' button.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the main window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

